    <title>PHP Debugging: Show all levels in vardump</title>
    <link href="https://tarik.io/en/languages/php/2017/06/18/php-debugging-show-all-levels-in-vardump/"/>
    <id>https://tarik.io/en/languages/php/2017/06/18/php-debugging-show-all-levels-in-vardump/</id>
    <published>2017-06-18T10:47:25.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-06-18T11:36:43.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>During PHP debugging, using <code>var_dump()</code> is a very common practice. <em>var_dump</em> limits its output if the object has many levels of children. You need to change some default values of xdebug to show full data.</p>
<p>You can change them on your <code>php.ini</code> file:<br><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">xdebug.var_display_max_depth = 15</div><div class="line">xdebug.var_display_max_children = 1024</div><div class="line">xdebug.var_display_max_data = 8192</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p>
<p>You can also set them on run-time, if you prefer avoiding a webserver restart. Put the code below before your <em>var_dump</em> call:<br><figure class="highlight php"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">ini_set(<span class="string">'xdebug.var_display_max_depth'</span>, <span class="number">15</span>);</div><div class="line">ini_set(<span class="string">'xdebug.var_display_max_children'</span>, <span class="number">1024</span>);</div><div class="line">ini_set(<span class="string">'xdebug.var_display_max_data'</span>, <span class="number">8192</span>);</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure></p>
<p>Reference:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9998490/how-to-get-xdebug-var-dump-to-show-full-object-array" target="_blank" rel="external">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/9998490/how-to-get-xdebug-var-dump-to-show-full-object-array</a></li>
</ul>
]]></content>
    
